rComments: She's kooky and funny but can be quite condescending in a way most art professors would be - your work will never live up to hers. However, she does her absolute best to aid her students in living up to their potential. She will give you all the tools you need - her teaching style is very clear so long as you understand French.

I found Ariane to be quite pleasant and caring of her students. Lots of time given to work on projects with very clear instructions on requirements. Arrive before nine and you're good. Don't take her class if you can't speak French well.

Honestly one of the worst teachers I've ever had. Treats her students like they are still in high school (threatens to take phones away). Does not explain the material well at all, grades according to who she likes most. Disrespectful and outright mean to her students. Class had potential to be interesting, she takes that all away. Avoid her.
ARIANE EST UNE TRES BONNE PROF POUR LES ETUDIANTS EN LEUR PREMIERE ANNÉE  LA CRITÈRE EST TRÈS CLAIRE ET EXPLICATION DE LA TECHNIQUE EST EFFICACE
